# PRD conventions

## File naming

`MM-DD-YYYY-topic-prd.md` (e.g. `04-03-2026-swc-church-app-prd.md`)

## Required structure

```markdown
# Title

**Version:** v1.0
**Last Updated:** Month DD, YYYY
**Author:** Name
**Status:** Draft | Active | Completed

---

## 1. Goal
## 2. Current State
## 3. Requirements
...numbered major sections with ## N.N subsections...

## N. Open Questions
```

**Key rules:**
- Use numbered top-level sections (`## 1.`, `## 2.`) and numbered subsections (`## 1.1`)
- Use tables for structured data (APIs, scope, checklists)
- Reference external URLs inline; use section symbols (e.g. **§16**) for internal cross-refs
- End with an **Open Questions** section for unresolved decisions
- If the PRD has UX surface, note that a design doc is needed and link to it once created
- If tickets are defined inline, extract them to `thoughts/tickets/` when implementation begins
